      • documentRendering

        public void documentRendering(NavigatorWindowEvent event)
        Description copied from interface: NavigatorWindowListener
        Invoked after a clientlet has set the document content. This could be when the document has rendered or is being rendered. This method is also called when a page error occurs.

        This method is meant to be used by the primary extension in order to update the address bar.

        Specified by:
        documentRendering in interface NavigatorWindowListener

        public void progressUpdated(NavigatorProgressEvent event)
        Description copied from interface: NavigatorWindowListener
        Invoked as a document loads in order to inform the listener of progress.

        This method is meant to be used by the primary extension in order to update its progress bar. It is invoked outside the GUI dispatch thread.
